<TITLE> Religious parties to go, in line with SC verdict: Shafique </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 27 (bdnews24.com)  Religion-based parties will be banned in line with the Supreme Court ruling on repeal of the Fifth Amendment, the law minister said on Saturday. "The Election Commission will move to cancel the registration of religion based parties after getting a copy of the verdict from the Appellate Division," minister Shafique Ahmed told a seminar at the Bangladesh Asiatic Society. The government will also take necessary measures to ban the parties, he said. The Supreme Court earlier this month upheld a 2005 High Court judgment declaring the Fifth Amendment illegal. The government has said the ruling cleared the way for restoration of the country's original constitution framed in 1972. Religion-based parties were banned in the 1972 constitution, but they were later reestablished through constitutional amendment. bd
